  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u2018\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'Country may be paralyzed'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Governor of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka Nandalal Weerasinghe has said that if a stable government is not formed soon the country may close down.",
        "Weerasinghe noted that there was much uncertainty as to whether sufficient foreign exchange would be found to pay for essential petroleum.",
        "Weerasinghe said progress in securing an international rescue package hinged on having a stable administration.",
        "Weerasinghe said that they have been able to finance at least three batches of diesel and one or two batches of petrol till the end of this month, and there is a lot of uncertainty as to whether they will be able to provide foreign exchange for the essential petroleum required by the country.",
        "Weerasinghe further mentioned that he needs a prime minister, a president and a cabinet that can take decisions, without which all the people will suffer.",
        "Weerasinghe said that if a stable government is formed, Sri Lanka will emerge from the crisis in three, four or five months."
      ],
